# **The Astra Flow - Service Level Agreement (SLA)**

---

Effective Date: October 1, 2025

Last Updated: October 1, 2025

**1. Introduction & Purpose**

This Service Level Agreement ("SLA") is entered into between The Astra Flow ("we", "us", "our") and **[Client Name]** ("you", "the client").

The purpose of this SLA is to define the level of service, support, and maintenance you can expect from us as part of your monthly Website-as-a-Service subscription. It outlines our commitments to you and your responsibilities as a client to ensure a successful and productive partnership. This document is a part of your binding contract with The Astra Flow.

**2. Definitions (Key Terms)**

- **"Minor Update":** A single task that can be completed by our technical team in **30 minutes or less**.
    - **Examples Include:** Changing text on a page, updating contact information (phone, address), swapping an image with one you provide, adding new photos to an existing gallery, making a minor change to a menu item.
    - **Examples Do NOT Include:** Creating a new page, adding a new feature (e.g., a booking form), significantly changing the layout or design of a page, graphic design work, or anything that requires more than 30 minutes of work.
- **"Support Request":** A request for technical assistance or a "Minor Update" submitted through the proper channels.
- **"Official Support Channels":** All requests must be submitted via email to **support@theastraflow.com** or through our client portal at **[Client Portal URL]**. Requests made via phone calls, WhatsApp, or social media will be redirected to these channels.
- **"Business Hours":** **9:00 AM to 5:00 PM GMT, Monday to Friday**, excluding all official Ghanaian public holidays.
- **"Response Time":** The time it takes for us to acknowledge your support request.
- **"Resolution Time":** The time it takes for us to complete the requested work or resolve the issue.

